<paragraph blockId="8.[138,1185,1565,1685]" pageId="8" pageNumber="271">
<emphasis box="[138,280,1565,1589]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="271">Relationship.</emphasis>
This species is very characteristic in having prescutellar setae, although it surely belongs to the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Okada" authorityYear="1968" box="[398,478,1597,1621]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Amiota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="271" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinuata">
<emphasis box="[398,478,1597,1621]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="271">sinuata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group by other diagnostic characters (body colour, length of aristal branches, broad hypandrium, shaped of paramere, etc.). This suggests a taxonomic relationship between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Okada" authorityYear="1968" box="[518,598,1661,1685]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Amiota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="271" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinuata">
<emphasis box="[518,598,1661,1685]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="271">sinuata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[659,777,1661,1685]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Amiota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="271" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apodemata">
<emphasis box="[659,777,1661,1685]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="271">apodemata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
groups.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[125,1024,136,160]" box="[125,1024,136,160]" pageId="9" pageNumber="272">
<emphasis box="[125,248,136,160]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="272">Etymology.</emphasis>
Referring to the outer membrane of aedeagus with fine serration.
</paragraph>
